replyContent: Sorry for the trouble!  This sometimes happens if an app fails to download completely, deleting and reinstalling the app may help.  If not, please contact us ( support@thup.com ) and let us know what kind of Android device you are using and will fix the issue ASAP.  We can also provide a refund in the meantime.

Galaxy Note 3 on T-Mobile with KitKat.  Impulse buy.  Help Milo and company navigate their way through a multi-tile path that requires you to identify numbers, letters, colors, shapes, furry objects, groceries and a large variety of categories.  Then race against a chinchilla, pick up some coins and get rewarded with a custom hat.  Way to go, THUP!

UPDATE:  Developers contacted me - and fixed the issue I was having on an older android device.  I got the update today and the play button is working perfectly on my tablet.  Thank you so much THUP games - VERY impressed by how seriously you took my complaint :)  I will be buying all the THUP monkey games as my 2 year old adores them so far.  Thank you very much!!    Original post:  My Daughter loves the Monkey apps - we started with Monkey Preschool lunchbox which she plays at childcare (she is not yet 3) so I got her this one for a bit of a change.  However, after any race, it says to hit the arrow to continue but there is never an arrow!  I have to exit the game and restart each and every time.  Please fix and I'll update my rating :)
replyContent: Sorry for the trouble!  Can you let me know what kind of Android device you are using?  We have tested on many phones and tablets and have not seen this issue, please contact us via email ( support@thup.com ) and we will find a fix ASAP!
